| The [[European Space Agency|ESA]] [[Planck (spacecraft)|Planck Surveyor]] was launched in May 2009. Over a four-year period, it performed a significantly more detailed investigation of cosmic microwave radiation than earlier investigations using [[High-electron-mobility transistor|HEMT]] [[radiometer]]s and [[bolometer]] technology to measure the CMB at a smaller scale than WMAP. On 21 March 2013, the European-led research team behind the Planck cosmology probe released the mission's data including a new CMB all-sky map and their determination of the Hubble constant.
